Date: 18 May 2013
Source: Standard Bred Canada
http://www.standardbredcanada.ca/notices/5-18-13/meadowlands-ontario-ehv-1-cases.html

Meadowlands On Ontario EHV-1 Cases
---------------------
As a result of the action taken by the Ontario Racing Commission (ORC) regarding the reported cases of Equine Herpes Virus-1 (EHV-1) at the Campbellville Training Centre in Ontario, the Meadowlands Racetrack, Tioga Downs and Vernon Downs will not accept entries of horses stabled at that location until further notice.

The ORC issued a notice on Friday stating no horses that are or were stabled at the Campbellville Training Centre from [29 Apr 2013] be allowed to race in Ontario until further notice following 2 confirmed cases of EHV-1 in the province.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-Mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org

[Equine Herpesvirus is a very contagious disease and is often deadly to the horses that contract it. Thus it can be devastating to the owners. The track is likely trying to protect itself as well as any horses under its care.

Ontario, Canada may be found on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at: http://healthmap.org/r/1*Y3 - Mod.TG]
